A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Making Georgia the No. 1 State for Tourism; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Georgia offers diverse tourism experiences from coastal retreats and mountain
4 escapes to small town charm and vibrant metro areas featuring a wide selection of hotels,
5 shopping centers, and dining experiences; and
6 WHEREAS, Georgia attracts visitors through local celebrations, family vacations, business
7 conferences, and sporting events; and
8 WHEREAS, Georgia is home to several major sports teams, including the Atlanta Falcons,
9 Atlanta Braves, Atlanta Hawks, Atlanta United, University of Georgia Bulldogs, Georgia
10 Tech Yellow Jackets, and Savannah Bananas, further enhancing tourism appeal; and
11 WHEREAS, Georgia's beaches, mountains, waterfalls, lakes, and scenic trails are natural
12 attractions that draw outdoors enthusiasts to this state; and
13 WHEREAS, Georgia boasts historic landmarks, museums, entertainment venues, and
14 business conferences, welcoming millions of visitors annually; and
