15 WHEREAS, increasing hotel stays boosts local economies, supports businesses, generates
16 tax revenue, and creates hospitality jobs; and
17 WHEREAS, encouraging in-state travel, including weekend getaways and staycations,
18 further stimulates economic activity; and
19 WHEREAS, Atlanta will host eight FIFA World Cup 2026 matches, and each match in
20 Atlanta is expected to generate $4.6 million in global media exposure, enhancing Georgia's
21 reputation as a premier travel destination; and
22 WHEREAS, despite ranking last in tourism marketing funding, Georgia has an opportunity
23 to elevate its profile during the 2026 FIFA World Cup; and
24 WHEREAS, this state has over 2,298 hotels, providing significant potential for economic
25 growth; and
26 WHEREAS, in 2023, Georgia's tourism industry generated a $79.7 billion state-wide
27 economic impact and over $5 billion in state and local tax revenue, supporting 463,000 jobs;
28 and
29 WHEREAS, youth sports represents a growing sector in tourism, attracting visitors and
30 creating new opportunities for economic growth for Georgia; and
31 WHEREAS, a study committee is necessary to identify tourism growth opportunities across
32 all regions, ensuring benefits for both small towns and large cities.
