33 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
34 (1) Creation of House study committee. There is created the House Study Committee
35 on Making Georgia the No. 1 State for Tourism.
36 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of ten members to be
37 appointed as follows:
38 (A) Five members from the House of Representatives to be appointed by the Speaker
39 of the House of Representatives, three of whom shall be selected from the Committee
40 on Economic Development and Tourism. The remaining two members shall be selected
41 from the House body based on their interest and expertise in tourism;
42 (B) One representative each from the Georgia Hotel and Lodging Association, Georgia
43 Association of Convention and Visitors Bureaus, Georgia Restaurant Association,
44 Georgia Sports Tourism Council, and Explore Georgia; and
45 (C) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall designate a legislative member
46 of the committee as chairperson of the committee.
47 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall assess tourism related challenges and
48 opportunities and recommend actions or legislation to support industry growth, with a
49 particular focus on increasing overnight hotel stays.
50 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
51 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
52 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
53 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
54 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
55 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
56 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
57 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
58 or who are state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the
59 committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
